# Monorepo / multi-package collaboration (organization template)

> **Per repository:** Document concrete paths (API server, SPA, OpenAPI, DB, codegen command) in this repo’s root **`AGENTS.md`**. This rule is generic.

## Ownership (default split — override in AGENTS.md if different)

- **Backend / API / DB / auth / uploads / business logic:** Cursor (or designated backend owner).
- **Frontend UI (layout, styling, visual UX):** Replit or frontend owner unless the task explicitly includes UI work.
- **HTTP contract:** Single source of truth (usually OpenAPI or equivalent). Server and client must match the spec.

## API contract

- Any new or changed route, query, or response shape **starts with** the spec, then codegen (if used), then implementation.
- **Do not hand-edit** generated SDK / Zod / OpenAPI-derived files; regenerate with the repo’s documented command.

## Safe changes

- Prefer **minimal, contract-safe** edits.
- Do not rename public HTTP paths or shared DTOs without updating the spec and consumers.

## Related template rules

When installed alongside this file: `org-api-spec.mdc`, `org-backend-api.mdc`, `org-database.mdc`.
